Dialogue: 10,0:00:37.75,0:00:42.82,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This morning, before work started \Nat the Daito Trading office, Toda Josei
Dialogue: 10,0:00:42.82,0:00:46.11,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was giving a lecture \Non political science for about an hour.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:47.26,0:00:52.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At Toda University—a comprehensive university without a physical campus—
Dialogue: 10,0:00:52.93,0:00:58.16,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto Shinichi studied \Na broad range of subjects under his master.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:58.67,0:01:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's wrap it up for today.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:01.44,0:01:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin-chan, are you reading anything right now?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:03.89,0:01:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm reading Whitman's poetry collection \Nand Tao Yuanming's Chinese poetry.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:08.29,0:01:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. It's because you're a poet in spirit. \NWhat about everyone else?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:14.99,0:01:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Just because you've gained Buddhist wisdom \Ndoesn't mean your education ends there. {lit: you can't become self-righteous just because you have the buddhism}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:20.60,0:01:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to keep studying all academic fields,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:23.10,0:01:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,including literature, and to learn \Nfrom the ideas and insights of great thinkers.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:27.96,0:01:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,At least because it lets you better understand the profundity of the Buddha Dharma.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:32.95,0:01:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Never slack off on your reading, gentlemen.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:35.76,0:01:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:36.76,0:01:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be returning to the headquarters now, \Nhave a good day.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:40.41,0:01:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We will, thank you very much. \NI'll also be at the headquarters in the afternoon.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:50.72,0:01:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, good morning!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:52.63,0:01:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, if it isn't Osabe-kun? How is your diner enterprise in Niigata doing? All good?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:58.10,0:02:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I found a great place to start from.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:02.37,0:02:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little far from the downtown area, \Nbut it's on the main street,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:06.77,0:02:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's the perfect place for a diner.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:09.99,0:02:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Good for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:12.76,0:02:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you once again \Nfor your help all those times.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:16.91,0:02:20.87,Top,,0,0,0,,What? You want to move to Niigata?\NThat's so out of blue...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:20.87,0:02:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it have something to do with your factory?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:24.29,0:02:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, my parents' company \Nwent bankrupt after a fire earlier this year.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:30.67,0:02:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I did my best to find new suppliers, \Nbut this recession has everyone at their wit's end.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:37.02,0:02:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been backed into a corner where shutting down the factory is my only option.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:42.45,0:02:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So what’s your plan if you go to Niigata?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:46.71,0:02:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a life set up there? {/any way to make a living}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:49.80,0:02:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,To be honest, I’d like to use this chance to start fresh and rebuild both my faith and my life
Dialogue: 10,0:02:55.18,0:02:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in Niigata from scratch.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:56.70,0:03:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,With the funds I have right now, \NI could set up a modest diner at best.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:02.22,0:03:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I use my experience as a chef \Nand run it solo, without hiring anyone,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:08.15,0:03:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe I can at least feed my family.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:11.63,0:03:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I can assure you it won't interfere \Nwith my work for Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:15.38,0:03:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The area that I am now in charge of \Nis centered around Niigata,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:21.45,0:03:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,so I'm sure it'll also be instrumental \Nin spreading the Common Path there.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:27.67,0:03:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, do you plan to stay in Niigata for good, \Nor are you just going there to test the waters?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:35.22,0:03:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't know until I go there...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:38.89,0:03:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Osabe-kun,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:41.56,0:03:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you're at liberty to go wherever you want \Nand do whatever you want for a living.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:47.17,0:03:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But when you say, "Since I'm going to keep helping the cause of the Common Path in Niigata,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:53.92,0:04:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the Buddha will naturally look after me," \Ndoesn’t that sound selfish and irresponsible?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:01.27,0:04:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,At least, that’s how it seems to me.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:02.98,0:04:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:05.52,0:04:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Believing you’ll get by just because you have faith is a distortion of what faith truly means.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:10.83,0:04:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Only by racking your brain \Nand working through sweat and tears
Dialogue: 10,0:04:14.55,0:04:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,will you make the impossible possible.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:16.94,0:04:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Only then will the Buddha's grace manifest itself \Nin one form or another without fail.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:22.77,0:04:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:24.38,0:04:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If you go to Niigata with the mindset that things will work out somehow, you should give up on it.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:30.27,0:04:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If you go, you have to be ready \Nto lay down your life.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:34.04,0:04:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Without that resolve, \Nwhat can you possibly accomplish?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:38.61,0:04:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you agree, Osabe-kun?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:41.81,0:04:44.67,Thought,,0,0,0,,All right, I'll lay down my life in Niigata, if needed.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:44.67,0:04:47.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,Only then will that yield any results! {よし 新潟に骨をうずめよう! そしてどれだけお役に立てるか}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.63,0:04:50.19,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's the choice of a lifetime for me! {これから生涯をかけてやってみよう!}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:51.12,0:04:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you resolved now?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:53.25,0:04:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:55.00,0:04:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. But let's not be hasty. \NYou need to get your feet wet first. {よし!だが焦るんじゃないよまず腰を据えることだ}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:59.61,0:05:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're still unable to make it work after that, then come see me again. {そして もしも どうにもこうにもならなくなったら そのときは私のところに来なさい}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:05.14,0:05:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll try to think of a better solution together. \NI'll be watching over you. {骨は拾ってあげよう 私はじっと君を見ているからね}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:14.11,0:05:18.19,Thought,,0,0,0,,Even sensei is ready to watch over me, \Na spineless weakling.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:18.19,0:05:21.81,Thought,,0,0,0,,I feel guilty. I have to give it my all, \Nno matter what...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:22.49,0:05:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:27.58,0:05:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So I bought the place \Nand decided to run a diner there.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:32.30,0:05:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Good for you. \NSo when are you moving in?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:36.00,0:05:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,May 26th.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:38.26,0:05:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There's not much time left. {もういくうもないな}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:41.40,0:05:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, let’s establish a new \NNiigata Division in the Mukojima Branch
Dialogue: 10,0:05:45.62,0:05:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and make you the District Chief!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:48.12,0:05:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Your wife can be the district chairwoman.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:51.52,0:05:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you do it?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:52.90,0:05:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, gladly!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:56.67,0:06:02.47,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Thus, the newly appointed District Chief Osabe moved to Niigata, resolved to lay down his life.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:02.47,0:06:06.14,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,His newly opened diner \Ngained a solid reputation for its food,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:06.14,0:06:09.73,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,and the number of regular customers steadily grew.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:10.98,0:06:14.08,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The proselytizing work in the area \Nalso picked up speed,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:14.08,0:06:17.19,Narrator,,0,0,0,,with nearly 200 households converting each month.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:17.19,0:06:24.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,By August, they were ready to invite President Toda to lead the first district general meeting.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:26.47,0:06:29.12,Top,,0,0,0,,Oh, Osabe-kun? How do you do?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:29.60,0:06:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m good, Sensei. The Niigata district \Nhas now reached over 600 households.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:34.91,0:06:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re just short of the 800-household goal you set for us.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:39.67,0:06:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Isn't it great? \NI expected nothing less.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:43.70,0:06:48.31,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Here in Niigata, thanks to Toda's stern, \Nfatherly guidance and encouragement,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:48.31,0:06:52.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,one member was able \Nto transform his life in a remarkable way. {I kinda get what muzu complains about here ngl}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:58.11,0:07:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That said, these next few weeks \Nlook really busy for you, Shin-chan.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:02.09,0:07:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The 2nd Hongo Branch general meeting \Nat the Chuo University Auditorium on the 22nd.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:07.45,0:07:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,May 31st-Headquarters Executive Meeting \Nat Toshima Public Hall.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:12.22,0:07:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,June 3rd-Women's Executive Meeting \Nat Shibuya Public Hall.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:16.90,0:07:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The 4th General Meeting of the Adachi Branch\Non the 5th, among other things.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:21.17,0:07:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And then a Men's Division executive meeting on the 7th, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.41,0:07:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:25.12,0:07:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll have to fly across the country \Nmore than ever before.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:31.12,0:07:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you handle it, Shin-chan?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:33.04,0:07:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do it!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:39.48,0:07:42.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This intense effort from Toda and Shinichi
Dialogue: 10,0:07:42.76,0:07:46.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,sparked an unprecedented surge \Nin the popularity of the Common Path. {episode title}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:52.34,0:07:57.56,Top,,0,0,0,,About that—you must all view yourselves \Nas upstanding citizens, not just pious believers. {ところで諸君は国士であって いわゆる宗教家ではない - lit: by the way, you are distinguished citizen; patriot, not religious leader; person of religion; religious figure; religionist - think he means "display your value to secular society before your piety"}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:57.56,0:08:02.50,Top,,0,0,0,,Any country can be saved with 100,000 \Nupstanding citizens gaining influence in it.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:03.07,0:08:05.51,Thought,,0,0,0,,100,000 upstanding citizens?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:06.02,0:08:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, when you say upstanding citizens, \Nare you saying we should all become politicians?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:12.96,0:08:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what I mean.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:14.83,0:08:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, some of you \Nwill find success as politicians.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:17.79,0:08:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But we can all be outstanding persons \Nin our own unique way,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:22.08,0:08:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,whether as economists, \Neducators, scientists or artists.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:26.53,0:08:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The upstanding citizens I’m referring to \Nare revolutionaries guided by the Mystic Law—
Dialogue: 10,0:08:31.20,0:08:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,individuals who, despite their different paths, \Nare attuned to the state of the nation
Dialogue: 10,0:08:36.37,0:08:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and the people’s suffering, \Nacting with sincere concern and selflessness.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:42.73,0:08:47.47,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,On June 11th, the second \NSuikokai outdoor training was held
Dialogue: 10,0:08:47.47,0:08:52.56,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,for two days and one night on the shores \Nof Lake Kawaguchi, one of the Fuji Five Lakes.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:03.36,0:09:05.90,Thought,,0,0,0,,There are no campsite facilities...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:10.43,0:09:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we staying there this time?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:12.97,0:09:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:14.35,0:09:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So even Suikokai is showing cracks now? {lit: became weak; frail; fragile}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:17.62,0:09:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:21.50,0:09:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I apologize deeply!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:28.27,0:09:29.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,C-Crud!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:30.45,0:09:35.46,Thought,,0,0,0,,Should we have stayed in a bungalow \Nor a tent, as Yamamoto-kun suggested?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:36.49,0:09:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, for the next question...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:38.95,0:09:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Fujikawa-kun.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:41.66,0:09:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, we often hear you say \N"Return home in glory," {to come home in triumph; to return to one's hometown in glory}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:45.65,0:09:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but how should we interpret it \Nfrom our perspective?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:49.74,0:09:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many different ways \Nto live a human life.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:53.68,0:09:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Leaving your hometown, working hard, achieving success, and returning to hear people say,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:59.43,0:10:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,"That snot-nosed kid from our town \Nhas grown into an outstanding young man,"
Dialogue: 10,0:10:03.67,0:10:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,must indeed be one of a man's \Ngreatest desires in this life.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:11.28,0:10:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The real question is, \N"What do you consider true glory?"
Dialogue: 10,0:10:16.33,0:10:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the fundamental question of your lives.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:21.14,0:10:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Does anyone here know what this glory is?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:24.56,0:10:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:27.40,0:10:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Becoming the top executive of a leading company or a government minister
Dialogue: 10,0:10:31.38,0:10:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,may seem glorious to society,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:34.74,0:10:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,but that kind of glory \Nis fleeting—it comes and goes.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:39.18,0:10:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Fujikawa's parents must be very happy \Nthat he became a ward assemblyman.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:45.13,0:10:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,People back home may be amazed and say, \N"Wow, you’ve brought glory to our hometown!"
Dialogue: 10,0:10:51.30,0:10:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,but that isn’t true glory.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:54.65,0:10:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Even Fujikawa's glory is not in that.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:58.12,0:10:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:58.89,0:11:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Fujikawa,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:00.18,0:11:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you're a ward assemblyman, but above all, \Nyou're an honorable Soka Gakkai executive!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:06.06,0:11:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If that is not glory, then what is?!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:11.28,0:11:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,As my disciple, and a Common Path devotee, \Nyou'll set foot in your hometown
Dialogue: 10,0:11:15.13,0:11:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,with the radiance of the highest and most enduring honor—that of a Soka Gakkai leader!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:21.30,0:11:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the ultimate glory \Nthat never fades or diminishes!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:25.82,0:11:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:27.71,0:11:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you get me, everyone?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:29.67,0:11:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:32.78,0:11:38.12,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,The traditional summer regional guidance was conducted for ten days from August 15th,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:38.12,0:11:44.65,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,with 632 high-ranking members from Tokyo \Nsent to 45 cities across the country.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:57.59,0:12:02.29,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Led by Yamamoto Shinichi, \Nthe eleven-member team in Sapporo
Dialogue: 10,0:12:02.29,0:12:07.16,Narrator,,0,0,0,,began each day with a 6 a.m. service \Nat their headquarters in Marushin Inn,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:07.16,0:12:09.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,followed by guidance and strategy meetings
Dialogue: 10,0:12:09.96,0:12:13.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and a full day of conversion and preaching activities.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:13.93,0:12:19.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In particular, Shinichi’s spirited lecture \Non the scriptures at the guidance meeting
Dialogue: 10,0:12:19.10,0:12:24.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was promptly relayed to the local cells gathered at each base of operations around 8 a.m.,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:24.41,0:12:27.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,reinvigorating them \Nwith the energy to keep fighting.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:28.16,0:12:31.01,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Sapporo city was split into five regions,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:31.01,0:12:34.52,Narrator,,0,0,0,,with roundtable discussions held \Nin each region in the day and evening.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:34.52,0:12:39.31,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Many newcomers attended and there was a steady stream of people wanting to join.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:39.83,0:12:41.64,Narrator,,0,0,0,,As the battle raged on,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.64,0:12:45.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Shinichi communicated via telegraph with all the chiefs of the Sapporo Cell
Dialogue: 10,0:12:45.67,0:12:50.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and had one of the group leaders \Ndrive him around the city on his scooter
Dialogue: 10,0:12:50.98,0:12:53.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to encourage their comrades at each base.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:53.36,0:12:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:54.80,0:12:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:55.90,0:12:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We were expecting you!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:00.96,0:13:04.72,Top,,0,0,0,,At the end of this ten-day battle, \Nthe Sapporo delegation
Dialogue: 10,0:13:04.72,0:13:11.65,Top,,0,0,0,,successfully converted 838 households, \Nfar surpassing their initial goal of 300,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:11.65,0:13:15.65,Top,,0,0,0,,and ranked first out of the 46 delegations.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:18.24,0:13:22.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This year marked the end \Nof the nationwide regional guidance trips,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:22.49,0:13:25.82,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but the success of the Sapporo Summer Campaign,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:25.82,0:13:29.83,Narrator,,0,0,0,,which achieved unprecedented results \Nunder Shinichi’s direction,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:29.83,0:13:33.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,would serve as a model for the following year’s \N1956 Battle of the Osaka Branch,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:33.58,0:13:37.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,setting an immortal milestone \Nin the history of Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:41.45,0:13:43.75,Thought,,0,0,0,,Hm, Kansai...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:44.37,0:13:46.81,Thought,,0,0,0,,What do we do about Kansai?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:52.44,0:13:56.07,Thought,,0,0,0,,This summer, the Osaka Branch \Nconverted 4,200 households.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:56.07,0:14:00.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,The Sakai Group in particular spread \Nthe Common Path to 436 households.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:02.38,0:14:08.34,Thought,,0,0,0,,Osaka is growing so fast that it is likely to overtake the oldest branch, Kamata.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:08.34,0:14:11.52,Thought,,0,0,0,,To make Kansai a major base,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:11.52,0:14:16.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,we must establish an assembly hall to serve as the headquarters for the Kansai Branch in Osaka.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:16.64,0:14:18.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,Then there's only one thing to do...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:19.47,0:14:24.17,Thought,,0,0,0,,Should we take the plunge and run our own candidate in the Osaka district elections?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:24.17,0:14:31.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,If it's a hopeless battle, the only way to win is with a surprise attack.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:31.41,0:14:37.40,Thought,,0,0,0,,The key is selecting the right leader \Nto carry out the surprise attack.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:38.04,0:14:42.77,Thought,,0,0,0,,If anyone can be trusted \Nwith this surprise attack,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:42.77,0:14:47.45,Thought,,0,0,0,,it’s Shinichi, who will lead us to victory \Nin line with my vision.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:48.10,0:14:50.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,At this point, we might as well let Shinichi
Dialogue: 10,0:14:50.64,0:14:53.92,Thought,,0,0,0,,walk the tough road of pioneering the Common Path in the region,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:53.92,0:14:56.46,Thought,,0,0,0,,regardless of whether he wins or loses.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.98,0:15:02.11,Thought,,0,0,0,,To test Shinichi's admirable courage \Nand brimming potential,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:02.11,0:15:07.40,Thought,,0,0,0,,there is no choice but to entrust him \Nwith the vast future of the Common Path...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:08.27,0:15:10.77,Thought,,0,0,0,,All right, I'll take this gamble.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:12.81,0:15:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We've decided to send representatives from the ranks of our cultural club
Dialogue: 10,0:15:16.77,0:15:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to the House of Councillors election \Nto be held next spring.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:20.23,0:15:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:23.19,0:15:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The selected candidates are
Dialogue: 10,0:15:25.20,0:15:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief Superintendent Harayama Koichi,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:27.95,0:15:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief Instructor Kiyohara Katsu,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:30.51,0:15:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Youth Division Chief Seki Hisao.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:33.62,0:15:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yessir!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.30,0:15:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:37.67,0:15:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Cultural Affairs Advisor Jujo Shunzo,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:40.63,0:15:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as the head of the Osaka Branch, \NHaruki Seiichiro—five people in total.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:45.39,0:15:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? In Osaka too?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:47.45,0:15:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't we getting ahead of ourselves?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:49.38,0:15:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I know you’re all thinking it’s a risky venture. \NIn fact, I’m not sure myself if it’s even achievable.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:56.06,0:15:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-Why are we doing it, then?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:57.69,0:16:01.25,Thought,,0,0,0,,When Sensei attempts something \Nthat seems impossible,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:01.25,0:16:04.07,Thought,,0,0,0,,there must be some hidden meaning to it.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.07,0:16:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you could call it a gamble,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.48,0:16:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but the reason I’m taking that risk is because \NKansai shows incredible promise.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:11.51,0:16:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So far this year, Kansai has surpassed Soka Gakkai’s most distinguished branch, Kamata,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:16.91,0:16:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,in conversion rate multiple times.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:19.77,0:16:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Kansai is where the surge is starting for us. {ep title again}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:22.38,0:16:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:25.62,0:16:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,In Osaka, a city of the common people \Nin the Kansai region,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:29.03,0:16:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to start a peaceful revolution that will return politics to the hands of the people.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:34.74,0:16:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think? Are you with me?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:37.50,0:16:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:38.73,0:16:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, the officer-in-chief, the one \Nwe’ll trust to secure victory in this election...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:44.35,0:16:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto-kun, it's you!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:46.92,0:16:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Affirmative.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:49.09,0:16:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They put him in charge \Nknowing damn sure they can't win...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:53.76,0:16:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope, the Branch Chief \Nunderstands the challenge here. {室長は厳しい実態を知っているのだろうか･･･?}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:57.60,0:17:01.73,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei trusts me to make \Nthe impossible possible.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:01.73,0:17:06.02,Thought,,0,0,0,,I should be grateful and fight hard \Nto live up to his expectations.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:06.02,0:17:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me tell you something.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:08.51,0:17:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,As you probably know, our political philosophy doesn’t align with either capitalism or socialism.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:15.58,0:17:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, it is a centrist humanism \Ngrounded in the precepts of Buddhism.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:20.48,0:17:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,To apply these ideals to people-oriented politics, we must enter the Diet,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:25.23,0:17:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the nation’s highest decision-making body,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:29.17,0:17:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and reform the political world from within to abolish politics driven by internal party agendas.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:35.37,0:17:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Japanese politics is currently \Nin a state of disarray that cannot be ignored.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:39.60,0:17:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why we must make haste.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:41.95,0:17:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I'm saying.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:44.05,0:17:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:56.35,0:17:59.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,We have to win no matter what...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:59.54,0:18:03.31,Thought,,0,0,0,,But how can we win this?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:03.31,0:18:08.82,Thought,,0,0,0,,In the fog of the impossible, there must be a path somewhere that leads to victory...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:14.72,0:18:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Clang-clang... {any onomatopoeia for the sound of a bell}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:18.35,0:18:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, it's done. \NLet's have a dinner now.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:21.62,0:18:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear, dinner is ready!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:42.89,0:18:44.04,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:51.13,0:18:52.63,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:52.63,0:18:56.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,You cannot win a battle if you, \Nthe one in command, are scared!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:02.06,0:19:06.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's not a strategy or a method, \Nit's faith and a prayer to the Lotus Sutra!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:20.91,0:19:23.85,Top,,0,0,0,,Yes... This is it!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:25.68,0:19:30.92,Thought,,0,0,0,,The key to making the impossible possible \Nis beautifully taught right here in the scriptures!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:30.92,0:19:34.68,Thought,,0,0,0,,Just like the battle in Sapporo, \Nif we keep studying the scriptures together,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:34.68,0:19:39.66,Thought,,0,0,0,,chanting the Sutra, and encouraging each other, \Nwe can make it in Osaka too!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:40.30,0:19:44.67,Thought,,0,0,0,,I only have the Lotus Sutra \Nand the scriptures to rely upon right now!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:46.31,0:19:50.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,During this time, Shinichi was responsible for lecturing in the Kansai region
Dialogue: 10,0:19:50.48,0:19:53.51,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and made several trips to Osaka each month.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:53.51,0:19:55.11,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,He began his preparatory work
Dialogue: 10,0:19:55.11,0:19:59.97,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,by encouraging his fellow believers in Kansai to study the scriptures.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:00.62,0:20:03.84,Top,,0,0,0,,Some of you may find \Nthe sacred scriptures hard to grasp,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:03.85,0:20:07.77,Top,,0,0,0,,but they are meant to be read repeatedly and reflected upon.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:08.83,0:20:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Without that, you can never learn anything. \NYou have to put in effort.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:14.92,0:20:23.99,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The year 1955 marked a major turning point \Nin Japan's postwar politics.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:24.47,0:20:30.15,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In October, the divided Socialist Party of Japan, once split into left and right wings, unified.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:30.15,0:20:34.33,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In response, the Liberal Party and the Democratic Party
Dialogue: 10,0:20:34.33,0:20:37.63,Narrator,,0,0,0,,merged to form \Nthe Liberal Democratic Party in November.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:37.63,0:20:41.59,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This marked the establishment of the so-called "55 System,"
Dialogue: 10,0:20:41.59,0:20:44.29,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and a political system \Nwith two opposing parties—
Dialogue: 10,0:20:44.29,0:20:46.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the LDP and the Socialist Party—\Ncontinued thereafter.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:46.85,0:20:52.46,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Around this time, Soka Gakkai members \Nwere increasingly making inroads into society,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:52.46,0:20:58.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and with that, the slander and libel \Nagainst Soka Gakkai in the media
Dialogue: 10,0:20:58.84,0:21:01.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,grew more intense and insidious.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:01.89,0:21:05.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Naturally, the articles were malicious hoaxes,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:05.20,0:21:09.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,based solely on the reporters' speculations \Nwithout any fact-checking.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:09.49,0:21:11.77,Narrator,,0,0,0,,All this negative press
Dialogue: 10,0:21:11.77,0:21:17.52,Narrator,,0,0,0,,has created a false impression \Nof Soka Gakkai in the minds of the people.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:17.52,0:21:20.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Culminating in a singular incident...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:23.24,0:21:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:24.18,0:21:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,"The {Director-General of the }Public Security{ Intelligence} Agency will monitor Soka Gakkai under the Subversive Activities {Prevention }Act"? {「学会を破防法で取り締まる」と公安調査庁長官が語っただって?}{https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Public_Security_Intelligence_Agency}{to enforce; to regulate; to supervise; to oversee; to command}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:29.51,0:21:34.46,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's inconceivable that Soka Gakkai's proselytizing {and propagation of religion }would violate the Subversive Activities {Prevention }Act.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:34.46,0:21:36.90,Thought,,0,0,0,,How could a movement to bring people happiness
Dialogue: 10,0:21:36.90,0:21:41.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,fall into the same legal category \Nas a revolutionary organization? {lit: why does it have to be cracked down on like the movements that try to overthrow the state}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:41.88,0:21:43.66,Thought,,0,0,0,,This is just unnatural...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:44.32,0:21:48.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,This is a statement that we in Soka Gakkai\N absolutely cannot let slide.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:51.94,0:21:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Yamamoto speaking.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:54.21,0:21:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes. I've read it.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:57.36,0:22:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If this is true, we're in serious trouble.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:02.24,0:22:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood. I'll verify its authenticity. \NWe'll take action right away.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:08.29,0:22:13.08,Thought,,0,0,0,,As always, I'm amazed \Nat how quickly Sensei reacted to it.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:13.08,0:22:17.81,Thought,,0,0,0,,If I hadn't read through that newspaper, \Nhe'd have admonished me again. {新聞に目を通していなかったらまたお叱りを受けるところだった}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:17.81,0:22:21.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,We must be ready at all times \Nto take immediate action...
Dialogue: 10,0:22:24.64,0:22:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,First, lawyer Ozawa will meet \Nwith the Director-General of the {Public Security Intelligence }Agency
Dialogue: 10,0:22:28.64,0:22:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to verify whether he actually said that.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:30.91,0:22:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,When we find that out, \Nwe'll contact the newspaper companies.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:33.88,0:22:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. So when will that meeting take place?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:38.19,0:22:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They promised to meet us as soon as possible, but since the Director-General is very busy,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:43.43,0:22:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the date has yet to be decided.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:45.17,0:22:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Too passive! {lax; lenient; slow}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:47.30,0:22:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the Director-General himself who made such an outrageous remark.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:51.66,0:22:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we just going to let him get away with it?!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:54.26,0:22:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Reading this article, it's clear
Dialogue: 10,0:22:56.40,0:23:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,he made that overbearing statement without any real understanding of Soka Gakkai's true nature.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:02.24,0:23:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don’t take a firm stand and refute it now, \Nthis nonsense will take root in the public’s mind.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:08.68,0:23:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn’t bother or sting me personally, \Nbut I feel sorry for our comrades. {/Soka Gakkai member}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:13.24,0:23:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm deeply sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:18.38,0:23:26.38,Top,,0,0,0,,The Subversive Activities Prevention Act, originally passed in 1952,
Dialogue: 10,0:23:26.38,0:23:30.05,Top,,0,0,0,,sparked uproar and confusion in the Diet.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:30.05,0:23:38.86,Top,,0,0,0,,It narrowly passed after a clause was added stipulating that it could only be enforced
Dialogue: 10,0:23:38.86,0:23:50.08,Top,,0,0,0,,against violent groups that undermined national institutions or disrupted public order.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:51.43,0:23:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm saying is, \Nwhen and where has our Soka Gakkai
Dialogue: 10,0:23:55.44,0:24:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,ever challenged national institutions? \NWhen have we ever disrupted public order?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:01.02,0:24:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Newspapers and magazines, \Nunwilling to make the proper effort
Dialogue: 10,0:24:05.30,0:24:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand the nature of Soka Gakkai,
Dialogue: 10,0:24:07.42,0:24:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,are only interested in publishing one-sided and baseless articles,
Dialogue: 10,0:24:11.06,0:24:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,like "new militant religion" or "they vandalized Shinto shrines and Buddhist altars."
Dialogue: 10,0:24:15.69,0:24:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai rejects violence, especially \Nas a means of carrying out its missionary work!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:22.40,0:24:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure all of you \Nalready know that well enough.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:26.98,0:24:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Good job out there.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:28.33,0:24:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So how did it go?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:30.43,0:24:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized something incredible.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:33.28,0:24:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:34.33,0:24:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The Director-General said, "I have never specifically mentioned Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:40.48,0:24:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If I did, bring it to me on tape or something."
Dialogue: 10,0:24:44.05,0:24:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But then...
Dialogue: 10,0:24:45.57,0:24:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. This article is a complete fabrication \Nfrom start to finish.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:49.47,0:24:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, would it be all right for us to ask \Nthe newspaper for an apology and a correction?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:55.95,0:25:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly. \NWe must take decisive action.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:00.06,0:25:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If they decide to fight back,
Dialogue: 10,0:25:02.12,0:25:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,we might as well subpoena the Director-General to let him clear his name.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:07.11,0:25:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand. I'll take action \Nand get in touch with the newspaper at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:15.18,0:25:19.37,Top,,0,0,0,,I thought it was the duty \Nof newspapers to report the truth.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:19.81,0:25:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Our lawyer contacted the Director-General directly and requested confirmation.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:27.51,0:25:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, "I have never specifically mentioned Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:30.84,0:25:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If I did, bring it to me on tape or something."
Dialogue: 10,0:25:35.81,0:25:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, what was the basis \Nfor this article from Chiba?
Dialogue: 10,0:25:41.29,0:25:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I'd like to hear.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:43.02,0:25:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what happened?\NIs it as he says?
Dialogue: 10,0:25:46.98,0:25:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:25:49.13,0:25:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The Director-General assured us we're in the clear. {lit: does not touch - meaning the law doesn't concern soka gakkai}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:51.93,0:25:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So why does your article clearly state that Soka Gakkai "violates the Subversive Activities Law"?
Dialogue: 10,0:25:56.65,0:25:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't this a blatant fabrication?
Dialogue: 10,0:25:58.64,0:26:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, if that's all true, you're quite right.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:02.77,0:26:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure you heard the Director-General say it?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:07.23,0:26:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If you stay silent, we'll never \Nget to the truth! Speak up!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:10.86,0:26:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it really all as he says—
Dialogue: 10,0:26:12.80,0:26:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you made it all up?!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:19.50,0:26:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems everything is as you say. \NIt was a fabrication.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:23.21,0:26:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Then publish a correction in the next issue, \Nstating that the article was unfounded.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:27.28,0:26:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Well, we...
Dialogue: 10,0:26:29.92,0:26:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you backing down now?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:32.01,0:26:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You caused a lot of trouble to Soka Gakkai by publishing material that is contrary to the truth.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:37.05,0:26:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't this the natural \Ncourse of action for a newspaper?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:40.93,0:26:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that is a company decision, \Nso it's not up to me...
Dialogue: 10,0:26:45.98,0:26:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Then consult with your higher-ups right now, please.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:51.94,0:26:56.74,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,While Shinichi was engaged in heated negotiations as the head of public relations,
Dialogue: 10,0:26:56.74,0:27:01.15,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Toda was in Osaka, attending the induction ceremony for the Kansai Headquarters.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:01.79,0:27:04.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The headquarters building was a three-story structure,
Dialogue: 10,0:27:04.92,0:27:09.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,purchased from the Osaka Music School, renovated, and refurbished.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:09.48,0:27:11.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,With a new base of operations acquired,
Dialogue: 10,0:27:11.78,0:27:16.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the excitement of the Kansai members \Nreached new heights.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:16.03,0:27:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It is now up to you to protect our foothold in Osaka.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:20.51,0:27:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,For that, I am truly grateful to all of you.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:23.60,0:27:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Please honor the Dharma
Dialogue: 10,0:27:25.50,0:27:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Wish for the Prosperity of the Great Law, \Nenshrined in this headquarters,
Dialogue: 10,0:27:29.65,0:27:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and may it bless you in return. {大法興隆所願成就}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:32.99,0:27:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,May all of you find fulfillment \Nand happiness in your faith.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:37.63,0:27:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That is my wish for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:43.12,0:27:47.12,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In the following year of 1956, this stronghold of the Common Path in Western Japan
Dialogue: 10,0:27:47.12,0:27:49.82,Narrator,,0,0,0,,would become the headquarters from which Yamamoto Shinichi
Dialogue: 10,0:27:49.82,0:27:53.13,Narrator,,0,0,0,,would lead the great breakthrough in the Battle for Kansai. {/great strides/great leap forward}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:53.88,0:27:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,As I reported over the phone earlier,
Dialogue: 10,0:27:56.63,0:28:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the newspaper has finally admitted their mistake and published a correction on December 14th.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:05.48,0:28:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, well done. But we can definitely expect more of these to pop up from now on.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:11.37,0:28:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The bigger Soka Gakkai gets, the more malicious the libel we'll face will become.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:17.05,0:28:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But we can't take a single step back.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:19.60,0:28:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:21.58,0:28:24.52,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,On December 23rd, as the year drew to a close,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:25.01,0:28:28.52,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,the last headquarters executive meeting of the year was held.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:28.52,0:28:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Through everyone's combined efforts,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:30.35,0:28:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,we have managed to spread the Lotus Sutra to 194,000 households over the past year.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:34.48,0:28:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The nationwide target of 300,000 households \Nhas been achieved with ease. {目標の総世帯数30万も悠々と突破し}
Dialogue: 10,0:28:38.88,0:28:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This provides a solid foundation \Nfor our next goal of 750,000 households. {これで75万世帯への基盤がしっかりと固まりました}
Dialogue: 10,0:28:43.51,0:28:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We aim to reach 500,000 next year \Nand hope you will make it your goal as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:49.42,0:28:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you do it, friends?
Dialogue: 10,0:29:01.55,0:29:05.35,Thought,,0,0,0,,How should we proceed \Nwith next year's Battle for Osaka?
Dialogue: 10,0:29:05.35,0:29:10.23,Thought,,0,0,0,,The combined Osaka and Sakai branch currently boasts 54,000 households,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:10.23,0:29:12.99,Thought,,0,0,0,,making it the largest \Nregional branch of Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:12.99,0:29:17.32,Thought,,0,0,0,,However, within Osaka Prefecture alone, \Nonly 31,000 households have been converted.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:17.32,0:29:20.80,Thought,,0,0,0,,As arrayed the current battle \Nis not in our favor.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:20.80,0:29:23.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,We need at least twice \Nthat number of households,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:23.41,0:29:26.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,and then we also need to gather \N50,000 motivated followers somewhere... {lit: at least 50000 first-class fighters (for); champions (of);}
Dialogue: 10,0:29:26.89,0:29:31.30,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's the basic condition for winning. \NAnd for that...
Dialogue: 10,0:29:31.84,0:29:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:33.25,0:29:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, are you okay?\NDid you catch a cold?
Dialogue: 10,0:29:37.03,0:29:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mind me. \NIt's nothing serious.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:39.74,0:29:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But you look really worn out...
Dialogue: 10,0:29:42.71,0:29:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, I'm not the type \Nto go down so easily.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:46.33,0:29:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:52.67,0:29:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, life is full of worry.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:58.23,0:30:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You only understand faith \Nwhen you start worrying. {悩んで初めて信心も分かるんだよ}
Dialogue: 10,0:30:03.20,0:30:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's how you pave your way \Nto greatness, Shinichi.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:07.41,0:30:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:09.27,0:30:11.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei has such keen insight into life.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:11.89,0:30:13.90,Thought,,0,0,0,,What a blessing...
Dialogue: 10,0:30:13.90,0:30:18.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,My life only feels so meaningful \Nthanks to I him looking after me.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:18.88,0:30:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a tough battle ahead, Shin.  \NBut don’t lose heart—keep fighting!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:25.14,0:30:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I will!
